                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d120">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.4111/1235</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Aide-Mémoire</hi>
                </p>
                <p>His Majesty’s Government are proposing to attach to the British Embassy in
                    Washington an Indian official with the rank of Minister. It is proposed that he
                    should be designated Agent General for India in the United States if the United
                    States Government have no objections to this title. His functions will be to
                    advise the Embassy on Indian affairs and to deal with non-political questions in
                    Indo-American relations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-17">April 17,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
